<title>ARGENTINA: Argentine MerVal index adds one stock in Q2.</title>
<headline>Argentine MerVal index adds one stock in Q2.</headline>
<dateline>BUENOS AIRES 1997-04-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Buenos Aires Stock Exchange announced Tuesday the addition of cement company Juan Minetti in its quarterly revision of the blue-chip MerVal index.</p>
<p>The inclusion of Juan Minetti takes the number of stock-listed firms that make up the MerVal to 25 from 24.</p>
<p>Following is a list of the stocks and their percentage weightings in the index:</p>
<p>    Acindar				11.13</p>
<p>    Perez Companc			 9.10</p>
<p>    Siderca				 7.90</p>
<p>    Alpargatas			    7.40</p>
<p>    Ciadea				  6.10</p>
<p>    Astra				   6.03</p>
<p>    YPF				     5.97</p>
<p>    Indupa				  4.98</p>
<p>    Telefonica			    3.76</p>
<p>    Molinos Rio de la Plata	   3.54</p>
<p>    Siderar				 3.39</p>
<p>    Comercial del Plata		 3.38</p>
<p>    Telecom				 3.25</p>
<p>    Banco Galicia			 3.10</p>
<p>    Banco Frances			 2.93</p>
<p>    Central Costanera		   2.45</p>
<p>    Sevel				   2.14</p>
<p>    Bansud				  2.08</p>
<p>    IRSA				    1.98</p>
<p>Transportadora del Gas del Sur	1.94</p>
<p>    Central Puerto			1.81</p>
<p>    Garovaglio			    1.80</p>
<p>    Celulosa				1.44</p>
<p>    Juan Minetti			  1.33</p>
<p>    Polledo				 1.12</p>
<p>((--Axel Bugge, Buenos Aires Newsroom, 541 318-0668))</p>
